{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863333244,"sessionID":"ses_2864e9e5fffeybhtzWMXF9IT3H","part":{"id":"prt_d79b40115001fz73gl0Q05sMPb","messageID":"msg_d79b26d1900146Q150Wo65H68J","sessionID":"ses_2864e9e5fffeybhtzWMXF9IT3H","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f0fc0118be3946889aee5750f3350a69","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-019: CLI ‰∫åËøõÂà∂ÂÖ•Âè£ (4 binaries) Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document describes the implementation of four CLI binary entry points for the AgentCube project. These binaries serve as the core executable components of the system, providing:\n\n1. **agentd** - Kubernetes controller for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n2. **picod** - HTTP server providing secure code interpreter execution environment\n3. **workloadmanager** - RESTful API server for sandbox creation and session management\n4. **agentcube-router** - Intelligent HTTP router for request routing and session management\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube platform requires four distinct binary entry points to manage different aspects of the system:\n\n- **agentd**: Uses controller-runtime framework to reconcile Kubernetes custom resources\n- **picod**: Provides file management and code execution APIs within isolated workspace jails\n- **workloadmanager**: Manages sandbox pods, sessions, and resource allocation through REST APIs\n- **agentcube-router**: Routes HTTP requests to appropriate sandbox instances based on session IDs\n\nCurrently, only `agentd` and `picod` binary entry points are implemented. This AR adds the remaining two entry points (`workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router`) and standardizes all four entry points with consistent patterns.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Overview\n\n```\n‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê\n‚îÇ                     Kubernetes Cluster                          ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ                                                                  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ     agentd       ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ workloadmanager  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ agentcube-      ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ   (Controller)   ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ   (API Server)   ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ    router       ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                 ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ Reconciler     ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ REST API       ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ HTTP Routing  ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ Leader Election‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ Session Mgmt   ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ JWT Auth      ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ Health Checks  ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ K8s Integration‚îÇ  ‚îÇ ‚Ä¢ Redis Store   ‚îÇ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚î¨‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò‚îÇ\n‚îÇ           ‚îÇ                     ‚îÇ                     ‚îÇ          ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ           ‚ñº                     ‚ñº                     ‚ñº          ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                    Kubernetes API Server                   ‚îÇ ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ AgentRuntime CRD  ‚Ä¢ CodeInterpreter CRD  ‚Ä¢ Pods        ‚îÇ ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò ‚îÇ\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò\n                           ‚îÇ\n                           ‚îÇ\n‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñº‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê\n‚îÇ                    Sandbox Pods (PicoD Daemon)                 ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îå‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îê  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ                    picod (per pod)                       ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ File Management API                                   ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ Workspace Jail                                        ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îÇ  ‚Ä¢ JWT Authentication                                    ‚îÇ  ‚îÇ\n‚îÇ  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò  ‚îÇ\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò\n```\n\n### Binary Entry Points\n\n| Binary | Path | Purpose | Package |\n|--------|------|---------|---------|\n| agentd | `cmd/agentd/` | Kubernetes controller | `pkg/agentd` |\n| picod | `cmd/picod/` | File management daemon | `pkg/picod` |\n| workloadmanager | `cmd/workloadmanager/` | Workload management API | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| agentcube-router | `cmd/agentcube-router/` | HTTP routing proxy | `pkg/router` |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### agentd Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    MetricsAddr          string\n    ProbeAddr            string\n    EnableLeaderElection bool\n    LeaderElectionID     string\n}\n\ntype Flags struct {\n    metricsBindAddress   string\n    healthProbeBindAddress string\n    leaderElect          bool\n}\n```\n\n### picod Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int\n    Workspace string\n}\n\ntype Flags struct {\n    port      int\n    workspace string\n}\n```\n\n### workloadmanager Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port              int\n    RedisAddr         string\n    RedisPassword     string\n    RedisDB           int\n    KubeconfigPath    string\n    MetricsAddr       string\n    ProbeAddr         string\n    EnableLeaderElection bool\n}\n\ntype Flags struct {\n    port              string\n    redisAddr         string\n    redisPassword     string\n    redisDB           int\n    kubeconfig        string\n    metricsBindAddress string\n    healthProbeBindAddress string\n    leaderElect       bool\n}\n```\n\n### agentcube-router Configuration\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  int\n    WorkloadManagerURL    string\n    RedisAddr             string\n    RedisPassword         string\n    RedisDB               int\n    JWTSecretName         string\n    JWTTokenExpiration    time.Duration\n    RequireAuth           bool\n    MetricsAddr           string\n}\n\ntype Flags struct {\n    port                  string\n    workloadManagerURL    string\n    redisAddr             string\n    redisPassword         string\n    redisDB               int\n    jwtSecretName         string\n    jwtTokenExpiration    string\n    requireAuth           bool\n    metricsBindAddress    string\n}\n```\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. agentd Binary Entry Point\n\n**File**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n\n**Purpose**: Initialize and start the Kubernetes controller manager.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    var metricsAddr string\n    var enableLeaderElection bool\n    var probeAddr string\n\n    flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n        \"The address the metric endpoint binds to.\")\n    flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n        \"The address the probe endpoint binds to.\")\n    flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n        \"Enable leader election for controller manager.\")\n\n    opts := zap.Options{\n        Development: true,\n    }\n    opts.BindFlags(flag.CommandLine)\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    ctrl.SetLogger(zap.New(zap.UseFlagOptions(&opts)))\n\n    mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n        Scheme:                 scheme,\n        HealthProbeBindAddress: probeAddr,\n        LeaderElection:         enableLeaderElection,\n        LeaderElectionID:       \"agentd-leader\",\n    })\n    if err != nil {\n        setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to start manager\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n\n    if err = (&agentd.Reconciler{\n        Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n        Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n    }).SetupWithManager(mgr); err != nil {\n        setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to create controller\", \"controller\", \"Agentd\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n\n    if err := mgr.AddHealthzCheck(\"healthz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n        setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up health check\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n\n    if err := mgr.AddReadyzCheck(\"readyz\", healthz.Ping); err != nil {\n        setupLog.Error(err, \"unable to set up ready check\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n\n    setupLog.Info(\"starting manager\")\n    if err := mgr.Start(signals.SetupSignalHandler()); err != nil {\n        setupLog.Error(err, \"problem running manager\")\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Controller-runtime manager initialization\n- Reconciler registration for AgentRuntime resources\n- Health and readiness probe endpoints\n- Prometheus metrics endpoint\n- Leader election support\n- Graceful shutdown handling\n\n### 2. picod Binary Entry Point\n\n**File**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n\n**Purpose**: Initialize and start the PicoD HTTP server.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    initFlags()\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    config := picod.Config{\n        Port:      GetPort(),\n        Workspace: GetWorkspace(),\n    }\n\n    server, err := picod.NewServer(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    go func() {\n        if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n\n    quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n    <-quit\n\n    klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- HTTP server initialization with configurable port\n- Workspace directory configuration\n- Graceful shutdown with timeout\n- klog integration for logging\n\n### 3. workloadmanager Binary Entry Point\n\n**File**: `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n\n**Purpose**: Initialize and start the Workload Manager API server.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    var port string\n    var redisAddr, redisPassword string\n    var redisDB int\n    var kubeconfig string\n    var metricsAddr, probeAddr string\n    var enableLeaderElection bool\n\n    flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n    flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n        \"Redis server address\")\n    flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n        \"Redis server password\")\n    flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n    flag.StringVar(&kubeconfig, \"kubeconfig\", \"\",\n        \"Path to kubeconfig file (optional, in-cluster config if empty)\")\n    flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n        \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n    flag.StringVar(&probeAddr, \"health-probe-bind-address\", \":8081\",\n        \"The address the probe endpoint binds to\")\n    flag.BoolVar(&enableLeaderElection, \"leader-elect\", false,\n        \"Enable leader election\")\n\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    ctx := context.Background()\n\n    redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n        DB:       redisDB,\n    })\n\n    if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    var kubeConfig *rest.Config\n    var err error\n    if kubeconfig != \"\" {\n        kubeConfig, err = clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", kubeconfig)\n    } else {\n        kubeConfig, err = rest.InClusterConfig()\n    }\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(kubeConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes clientset: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    wmConfig := workloadmanager.Config{\n        Port:          port,\n        RedisClient:   redisClient,\n        K8sClient:     clientset,\n        MetricsAddr:   metricsAddr,\n        ProbeAddr:     probeAddr,\n    }\n\n    server, err := workloadmanager.NewServer(ctx, wmConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    go func() {\n        if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n\n    quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n    <-quit\n\n    klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Redis client initialization with health check\n- Kubernetes client initialization (in-cluster or kubeconfig)\n- RESTful API server with configurable port\n- Health probe endpoints\n- Prometheus metrics endpoint\n- Leader election support\n- Graceful shutdown with timeout\n\n### 4. agentcube-router Binary Entry Point\n\n**File**: `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n\n**Purpose**: Initialize and start the Router HTTP server.\n\n**Implementation**:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    var port string\n    var workloadManagerURL, redisAddr, redisPassword string\n    var redisDB int\n    var jwtSecretName, jwtTokenExpiration string\n    var requireAuth bool\n    var metricsAddr string\n\n    flag.StringVar(&port, \"port\", \"8080\", \"Port to listen on\")\n    flag.StringVar(&workloadManagerURL, \"workload-manager-url\",\n        \"http://localhost:8080\", \"Workload manager URL\")\n    flag.StringVar(&redisAddr, \"redis-addr\", \"localhost:6379\",\n        \"Redis server address\")\n    flag.StringVar(&redisPassword, \"redis-password\", \"\",\n        \"Redis server password\")\n    flag.IntVar(&redisDB, \"redis-db\", 0, \"Redis database number\")\n    flag.StringVar(&jwtSecretName, \"jwt-secret-name\",\n        \"picod-router-identity\", \"Kubernetes secret name for JWT keys\")\n    flag.StringVar(&jwtTokenExpiration, \"jwt-token-expiration\", \"5m\",\n        \"JWT token expiration duration\")\n    flag.BoolVar(&requireAuth, \"require-auth\", false,\n        \"Require JWT authentication for all requests\")\n    flag.StringVar(&metricsAddr, \"metrics-bind-address\", \":8080\",\n        \"The address the metric endpoint binds to\")\n\n    klog.InitFlags(nil)\n    flag.Parse()\n\n    ctx := context.Background()\n\n    redisClient := redis.NewClient(&redis.Options{\n        Addr:     redisAddr,\n        Password: redisPassword,\n        DB:       redisDB,\n    })\n\n    if err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    k8sConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    k8sClient, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(k8sConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create kubernetes client: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    expiration, err := time.ParseDuration(jwtTokenExpiration)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to parse JWT token expiration: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    routerConfig := router.Config{\n        Port:               port,\n        WorkloadManagerURL: workloadManagerURL,\n        RedisClient:        redisClient,\n        K8sClient:          k8sClient,\n        JWTSecretName:      jwtSecretName,\n        JWTTokenExpiration: expiration,\n        RequireAuth:        requireAuth,\n        MetricsAddr:        metricsAddr,\n    }\n\n    server, err := router.NewServer(ctx, routerConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    go func() {\n        if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n            klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n\n    quit := make(chan os.Signal, 1)\n    signal.Notify(quit, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n    <-quit\n\n    klog.Info(\"Shutting down server...\")\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    if err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n    }\n\n    klog.Info(\"Server stopped\")\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Redis client initialization for session storage\n- Kubernetes client for JWT secret access\n- Workload Manager client for proxying requests\n- JWT authentication/authorization\n- HTTP routing based on session IDs\n- Prometheus metrics endpoint\n- Graceful shutdown with timeout\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Common Error Handling Patterns\n\nAll binaries follow consistent error handling patterns:\n\n1. **Fatal Errors**: Use `klog.Fatalf()` or `os.Exit(1)` for unrecoverable errors\n2. **Graceful Shutdown**: Handle SIGINT/SIGTERM signals for clean shutdown\n3. **Context Cancellation**: Use context with timeout for shutdown operations\n4. **Health Checks**: Implement health and readiness probes for monitoring\n\n### Startup Errors\n\n```go\n// Example: Redis connection failure\nif err := redisClient.Ping(ctx).Err(); err != nil {\n    klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to connect to Redis: %v\", err)\n}\n\n// Example: Kubernetes config failure\nkubeConfig, err := rest.InClusterConfig()\nif err != nil {\n    klog.Fatalf(\"Failed to get in-cluster config: %v\", err)\n}\n```\n\n### Runtime Errors\n\n```go\n// Example: Server runtime error\ngo func() {\n    if err := server.Run(); err != nil {\n        klog.Fatalf(\"Server error: %v\", err)\n    }\n}()\n\n// Example: Shutdown error\nif err := server.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n    klog.Fatalf(\"Server shutdown error: %v\", err)\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\nEach binary entry point should have unit tests covering:\n\n1. **Flag Parsing**: Verify command-line flags are correctly parsed\n2. **Configuration**: Verify configuration structs are correctly populated\n3. **Initialization**: Verify dependencies (Redis, Kubernetes) are correctly initialized\n4. **Error Handling**: Verify errors are properly handled and logged\n\n### Integration Tests\n\nIntegration tests should verify:\n\n1. **End-to-End Startup**: Complete startup sequence with all dependencies\n2. **Health Checks**: Health and readiness probes respond correctly\n3. **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics are exposed correctly\n4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Clean shutdown without resource leaks\n\n### Test Structure\n\n```\ncmd/agentd/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main_test.go\n\ncmd/picod/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main_test.go\n\ncmd/workloadmanager/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main_test.go\n\ncmd/agentcube-router/\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.go\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ main_test.go\n```\n\n## Build System\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n```makefile\n# Build all binaries\n.PHONY: build\nbuild: build-agentd build-picod build-workloadmanager build-router\n\n# Build individual binaries\n.PHONY: build-agentd\nbuild-agentd:\n\tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n\n.PHONY: build-picod\nbuild-picod:\n\tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\n.PHONY: build-workloadmanager\nbuild-workloadmanager:\n\tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workloadmanager\n\n.PHONY: build-router\nbuild-router:\n\tCGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags \"-s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)\" \\\n\t\t-o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/agentcube-router\n\n# Clean build artifacts\n.PHONY: clean\nclean:\n\trm -rf bin/\n```\n\n### Build Optimization\n\n- **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static binaries\n- **Strip Symbols**: `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to reduce binary size\n- **Version Injection**: `-X main.version=$(VERSION)` for version info\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\nAll binaries support environment variable configuration in addition to flags:\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | Metrics bind address for agentd | `:8080` |\n| `PICOD_PORT` | Port for picod server | `8080` |\n| `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | Workspace directory for picod | `/workspace` |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_PORT` | Port for workloadmanager | `8080` |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for workloadmanager | `localhost:6379` |\n| `ROUTER_PORT` | Port for router | `8080` |\n| `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Workload manager URL for router | `http://localhost:8080` |\n| `ROUTER_REDIS_ADDR` | Redis address for router | `localhost:6379` |\n\n### Kubernetes Deployment Configuration\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: workloadmanager\n  namespace: agentcube\nspec:\n  replicas: 2\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: workloadmanager\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: workloadmanager\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: workloadmanager\n        image: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n          name: http\n        - containerPort: 8081\n          name: health\n        - containerPort: 8080\n          name: metrics\n        env:\n        - name: PORT\n          value: \"8080\"\n        - name: REDIS_ADDR\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: redis-secret\n              key: address\n        - name: REDIS_PASSWORD\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: redis-secret\n              key: password\n        livenessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /healthz\n            port: health\n        readinessProbe:\n          httpGet:\n            path: /readyz\n            port: health\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            cpu: 100m\n            memory: 128Mi\n          limits:\n            cpu: 500m\n            memory: 512Mi\n```\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Metrics\n\nAll binaries expose Prometheus metrics on a dedicated port:\n\n- **agentd**: `:8080/metrics`\n- **picod**: `:8080/metrics` (if implemented)\n- **workloadmanager**: `:8080/metrics`\n- **agentcube-router**: `:8080/metrics`\n\n### Health Checks\n\n| Binary | Health Endpoint | Ready Endpoint |\n|--------|-----------------|----------------|\n| agentd | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n| picod | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n| workloadmanager | `:8081/healthz` | `:8081/readyz` |\n| agentcube-router | `:8080/health` | Not implemented |\n\n### Logging\n\nAll binaries use `klog` for structured logging with consistent format:\n\n```go\nklog.Info(\"Server started\")\nklog.Infof(\"Listening on port %d\", port)\nklog.Warningf(\"Connection failed: %v\", err)\nklog.Errorf(\"Fatal error: %v\", err)\n```\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Go Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"flag\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"os/signal\"\n    \"syscall\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/healthz\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log/zap\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager/signals\"\n)\n```\n\n### Package Dependencies\n\n| Binary | Package | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| agentd | `pkg/agentd` | Controller logic |\n| picod | `pkg/picod` | Server logic |\n| workloadmanager | `pkg/workloadmanager` | API handlers |\n| agentcube-router | `pkg/router` | Routing logic |\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Authentication\n\n1. **agentd**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n2. **picod**: JWT-based authentication (optional)\n3. **workloadmanager**: Uses Kubernetes service account authentication\n4. **agentcube-router**: JWT-based authentication with Kubernetes secret storage\n\n### Authorization\n\n1. **RBAC**: All binaries use Kubernetes RBAC for API access\n2. **Secret Access**: Limited access to required secrets only\n3. **Network Policies**: Restrict network access using Kubernetes network policies\n\n### Secure Defaults\n\n- Use in-cluster configuration when running in Kubernetes\n- Require explicit kubeconfig for local development\n- Use strong default passwords for Redis (from secrets)\n- Enable TLS for production deployments\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Resource Requirements\n\n| Binary | CPU Request | CPU Limit | Memory Request | Memory Limit |\n|--------|-------------|-----------|----------------|--------------|\n| agentd | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n| picod | 100m | 500m | 64Mi | 256Mi |\n| workloadmanager | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n| agentcube-router | 100m | 500m | 128Mi | 512Mi |\n\n### Optimization\n\n1. **Static Compilation**: `CGO_ENABLED=0` for faster startup\n2. **Binary Size**: Use `-ldflags \"-s -w\"` to strip symbols\n3. **Connection Pooling**: Redis and Kubernetes clients use connection pooling\n4. **Graceful Shutdown**: Proper cleanup of resources on shutdown\n\n## Deployment Strategy\n\n### Phase 1: Development (Week 1)\n\n- Implement `cmd/workloadmanager/main.go`\n- Implement `cmd/agentcube-router/main.go`\n- Update Makefile with new build targets\n- Unit tests for new binaries\n\n### Phase 2: Integration (Week 2)\n\n- Update Helm charts for new binaries\n- Configure RBAC permissions\n- Add health checks and probes\n- Integration tests\n\n### Phase 3: Staging (Week 3)\n\n- Deploy to staging environment\n- Monitor metrics and logs\n- Performance testing\n- Security review\n\n### Phase 4: Production (Week 4)\n\n- Deploy to production\n- Gradual rollout with feature flags\n- Monitor for issues\n- Full rollout\n\n## References\n\n- controller-runtime documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\n- klog documentation: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/klog/v2\n- Redis Go client: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n- Kubernetes client-go: https://pkg.go.dev/k8s.io/client-go\n\n## Appendix A: Complete Binary Configuration\n\n### agentd Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics endpoint address |\n| `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n| `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n\n### picod Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | `8080` | Server port |\n| `--workspace` | string | `/workspace` | Workspace directory |\n\n### workloadmanager Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n| `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n| `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n| `--kubeconfig` | string | `` | Kubeconfig path |\n| `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n| `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | `:8081` | Health probe address |\n| `--leader-elect` | bool | `false` | Enable leader election |\n\n### agentcube-router Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | string | `8080` | Server port |\n| `--workload-manager-url` | string | `http://localhost:8080` | Workload manager URL |\n| `--redis-addr` | string | `localhost:6379` | Redis address |\n| `--redis-password` | string | `` | Redis password |\n| `--redis-db` | int | `0` | Redis database |\n| `--jwt-secret-name` | string | `picod-router-identity` | JWT secret name |\n| `--jwt-token-expiration` | string | `5m` | JWT token expiration |\n| `--require-auth` | bool | `false` | Require authentication |\n| `--metrics-bind-address` | string | `:8080` | Metrics address |\n\n## Appendix B: Startup Sequence Diagrams\n\n### agentd Startup\n\n```\nmain()\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Parse flags\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Initialize logger (zap)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Create controller-runtime manager\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Load kubeconfig\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Create manager\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Set leader election config\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Register reconciler\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Add health checks\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ /healthz (liveness)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ /readyz (readiness)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Start manager\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Leader election (if enabled)\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Start controllers\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Graceful shutdown\n```\n\n### workloadmanager Startup\n\n```\nmain()\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Parse flags\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Initialize logger (klog)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Connect to Redis\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Ping to verify connection\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Create Kubernetes client\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ In-cluster config or kubeconfig\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Create clientset\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Create server\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Configure HTTP router\n‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Register handlers\n‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Setup metrics\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Start server (goroutine)\n‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Wait for signals (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Graceful shutdown\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Stop accepting new connections\n    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Wait for active connections (30s timeout)\n    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Close Redis and Kubernetes clients\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-019/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox_test.go\">\nERROR [148:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [248:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [358:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [419:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [509:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [541:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\nERROR [579:27] undefined: store.NewValkeyStore\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go\">\nERROR [77:50] too many arguments in call to sc.store.StoreSandbox\n\thave (context.Context, string, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\n\twant (context.Context, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\nERROR [120:51] too many arguments in call to sc.store.UpdateSandbox\n\thave (context.Context, string, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\n\twant (context.Context, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\".SandboxInfo)\nERROR [180:50] too many arguments in call to sc.store.StoreSandbox\n\thave (context.Context, string, *\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg